thread.title: Record number of Labor Day weekend travellers expected at Los Angeles International Airport
thread.title_full: Record number of Labor Day weekend travellers expected at Los Angeles International Airport - Winnipeg Free Press

author: The Associated Press
title: Record number of Labor Day weekend travellers expected at Los Angeles International Airport
text:
LOS ANGELES, Calif. - Los Angeles International Airport is expecting a record number of travellers during the Labor Day weekend.
An airport statement says 835,500 passengers are expected to pass through LAX Friday through Monday.
That's 7 per cent more than last year, which was also a record.
More than 310,600 vehicles are expected to enter the central terminal area during the weekend.
The airport is in the midst of a multibillion-dollar renovation. Five of the nine terminals and portions of the central terminal area roads, sidewalks and parking structures are under construction.
